{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Yang et al. [116] reported that autogenous shrinkage predominantly occurs during the early stages of concrete development, typically between 0 and 7 days, with significant shrinkage in the initial phase followed by a gradual decline.",
    "Similarly, Singh et al. [117] observed that about 85% of total shrinkage is achieved within the first 28 days.",
    "To mitigate shrinkage, various strategies have been explored.",
    "Researchers such as Alaskar and Hooton [118], along with Li et al. [119], Ling et al.",
    "[120], and Salami et al. [121], demonstrated that replacing sand with coal bottom ash at rates of 50%, 75%, or 100%, and substituting ordinary Portland cement (OPC) with 20% FA, significantly reduces drying shrinkage."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
